I now have a thorough understanding of every aspect of the codebase. Let me compile the comprehensive enhancement plan.

---

# Freedom Wall UI Enhancement Plan -- Comprehensive Design Specification

## Overview

This plan covers 8 enhancement areas for the Freedom Wall page (`C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\freedomWall\FreedomWallPage.jsx` and `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\freedomWall\freedomWall.css`). All changes are targeted, additive modifications that preserve the existing 2,789-line component structure. The Framer Motion import is added once at the top; the rest is wrapping existing JSX elements and adding CSS rules.

---

## AREA 1: Header Enhancement

### Current State (lines 2215-2244 of JSX)
The header renders a plain `<div className="freedom-wall-header">` containing:
- Title shell with `<h2>Freedom Wall</h2>`, subtitle `<p>`, and countdown pill
- Week shell with week pill, time capsule toggle button, and labels

### JSX Changes

**1a. Title with chalk glow effect.** Replace the `<h2>` element at line 2217:

```jsx
// BEFORE:
<h2 className="freedom-wall-title">Freedom Wall</h2>

// AFTER:
<h2 className="freedom-wall-title">
    <span className="fw-title-chalk">Freedom Wall</span>
</h2>
```

**1b. Active users indicator.** After the countdown pill (line 2223), add:

```jsx
<div className="freedom-wall-countdown-pill">
    Wall resets in: {countdownText}
</div>
{remoteCursorItems.length > 0 && (
    <div className="fw-active-users-pill">
        <span className="fw-active-dot" />
        {remoteCursorItems.length} active {remoteCursorItems.length === 1 ? "user" : "users"}
    </div>
)}
```

**1c. Segmented countdown timer.** Replace the countdown pill text rendering. The `countdownText` (from `formatResetCountdown`) returns strings like "2 days, 5 hours" or "3 hours, 12 mins". We can parse it to show segmented boxes. However, for minimal component change, simply add a CSS-animated clock icon and a segment styling approach:

At line 2221-2223, replace:
```jsx
// BEFORE:
<div className="freedom-wall-countdown-pill">
    Wall resets in: {countdownText}
</div>

// AFTER:
<div className="freedom-wall-countdown-pill">
    <span className="fw-countdown-icon">&#9201;</span>
    <span className="fw-countdown-label">Resets in</span>
    <span className="fw-countdown-value" key={countdownText}>{countdownText}</span>
</div>
```

The `key={countdownText}` will trigger CSS animation on every value change via the `:target` or CSS animation reset trick. We will handle animation purely via CSS `@keyframes` on `.fw-countdown-value`.

### CSS Changes

```css
/* ── Enhanced Title ── */
.fw-title-chalk {
    font-family: "Patrick Hand", "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    background: linear-gradient(
        180deg,
        rgba(240, 235, 228, 0.95) 0%,
        rgba(210, 205, 198, 0.85) 100%
    );
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(230, 225, 218, 0.2))
            drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(230, 225, 218, 0.08));
    text-shadow: none; /* override parent text-shadow for clip to work */
}

/* ── Active Users Pill ── */
.fw-active-users-pill {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(168, 230, 163, 0.25);
    background: rgba(168, 230, 163, 0.08);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--fw-chalk-green);
    font-weight: 600;
}

.fw-active-dot {
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--fw-chalk-green);
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(168, 230, 163, 0.4);
    animation: fw-pulse-dot 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes fw-pulse-dot {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 0.5; transform: scale(0.75); }
}

/* ── Enhanced Countdown Pill ── */
.freedom-wall-countdown-pill {
    /* Keep existing styles, add: */
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
}

.fw-countdown-icon {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    animation: fw-tick-wobble 1s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes fw-tick-wobble {
    0%, 100% { transform: rotate(0deg); }
    25% { transform: rotate(6deg); }
    75% { transform: rotate(-6deg); }
}

.fw-countdown-label {
    opacity: 0.7;
    font-weight: 500;
}

.fw-countdown-value {
    animation: fw-count-tick 0.3s ease-out;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
}

@keyframes fw-count-tick {
    0% { opacity: 0.5; transform: translateY(2px); }
    100% { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}

/* ── Header separator ── */
.freedom-wall-header {
    /* add to existing: */
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(220, 225, 220, 0.08);
}
```

---

## AREA 2: Toolbar Enhancement

### Current State (lines 2246-2357 of JSX)
Tool buttons render text only ("Doodle", "Sticker", etc.). The `TOOL_EMOJIS` constant exists at line 51 but is only used for the mobile FAB orb, not for button labels.

### JSX Changes

**2a. Add emoji prefixes to tool buttons.** At lines 2254-2258, update each button to include the emoji:

```jsx
// BEFORE:
<button ... className={`fw-tool-btn ${activeTool === "doodle" ? "is-active" : ""}`} ...>Doodle</button>

// AFTER:
<button ... className={`fw-tool-btn ${activeTool === "doodle" ? "is-active" : ""}`} ...>
    <span className="fw-tool-emoji">{TOOL_EMOJIS.doodle}</span> Doodle
</button>
```

Repeat for all 5 tool buttons: doodle, sticker, stamp, note, eraser.

**2b. Add visual divider between tool group and settings toggle.** Before the settings toggle button at line 2259, add a divider element:

```jsx
{!isMobileView && (
    <>
        <span className="fw-tool-divider" />
        <button
            type="button"
            className={`fw-tool-btn fw-popover-toggle ${isDockPopoverOpen ? "is-active" : ""}`}
            ...
        >
```

**2c. Wrap the popover controls panel with AnimatePresence.** The popover at line 2271 currently renders conditionally. Wrap it:

```jsx
// At the top of the file, add to import:
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from "framer-motion";

// Then at line 2271:
// BEFORE:
{(isMobileView || isDockPopoverOpen) && <div className="fw-dock-controls-popover">

// AFTER:
<AnimatePresence>
{(isMobileView || isDockPopoverOpen) && (
    <motion.div
        className="fw-dock-controls-popover"
        initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8, scale: 0.96 }}
        animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, scale: 1 }}
        exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 8, scale: 0.96 }}
        transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 420, damping: 22 }}
    >
```

And the closing at line 2355:
```jsx
// BEFORE:
</div>}{/* end popover / controls wrapper */}

// AFTER:
</motion.div>
)}
</AnimatePresence>
```

**2d. Mobile FAB pulse animation.** At line 2247, add the pulse class:

```jsx
// BEFORE:
<button type="button" className="fw-fab-orb" onClick={...}>

// AFTER:
<button type="button" className="fw-fab-orb fw-fab-pulse" onClick={...}>
```

### CSS Changes

```css
/* ── Tool Emoji ── */
.fw-tool-emoji {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin-right: 0.15rem;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: transform 0.15s;
}

.fw-tool-btn:hover .fw-tool-emoji {
    transform: scale(1.15);
}

.fw-tool-btn.is-active .fw-tool-emoji {
    animation: fw-tool-emoji-glow 1.5s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes fw-tool-emoji-glow {
    0%, 100% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 2px rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.15)); }
    50% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.35)); }
}

/* ── Active tool glow transition ── */
.fw-tool-btn.is-active {
    /* extend existing rule with: */
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.3s, transform 0.1s;
}

/* ── Tool Divider ── */
.fw-tool-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 22px;
    background: rgba(220, 225, 220, 0.12);
    margin: 0 0.15rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* ── Mobile FAB pulse ── */
.fw-fab-pulse {
    animation: fw-fab-ring 3s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes fw-fab-ring {
    0%, 100% {
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.35), 0 0 12px rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.12);
    }
    50% {
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.35), 0 0 20px rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.25), 0 0 40px rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.08);
    }
}
```

---

## AREA 3: Canvas Frame Enhancement

### Current State (CSS lines 328-374)
The canvas shell already has an `fw-ambient-pulse` animation, a border-image gradient frame, and a `::after` pseudo-element for vignette. There is also a `::before` grain overlay on `.freedom-wall-page`.

### CSS Changes Only

**3a. Chalk dust particles near top corners.** Add a new `::before` pseudo-element on the canvas shell for decorative chalk dust:

```css
.freedom-wall-canvas-shell::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 40px;
    z-index: 5;
    pointer-events: none;
    background:
        radial-gradient(
            circle at 8% 20%,
            rgba(230, 225, 218, 0.06) 0%,
            transparent 35%
        ),
        radial-gradient(
            circle at 92% 15%,
            rgba(230, 225, 218, 0.05) 0%,
            transparent 30%
        ),
        radial-gradient(
            circle at 5% 60%,
            rgba(245, 230, 163, 0.03) 0%,
            transparent 25%
        ),
        radial-gradient(
            circle at 95% 50%,
            rgba(163, 201, 245, 0.03) 0%,
            transparent 25%
        );
    animation: fw-dust-drift 12s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
}

@keyframes fw-dust-drift {
    0% { opacity: 0.7; }
    100% { opacity: 1; }
}
```

**3b. Slightly more visible grid.** The grid lines on the Konva canvas currently use `rgba(200, 195, 185, 0.04)`. Increase to `0.055` in the JSX at lines 2589 and 2597:

```jsx
// Line 2589 (vertical grid lines):
stroke="rgba(200, 195, 185, 0.055)"

// Line 2597 (horizontal grid lines):
stroke="rgba(200, 195, 185, 0.055)"
```

This is a minimal change: just updating two string literals from `0.04` to `0.055`.

---

## AREA 4: Draft Panels Enhancement

### Current State (lines 2359-2500 of JSX)
Three draft panels (note, sticker, stamp) render as `<div className="fw-draft-note-panel">`. They appear/disappear with conditional rendering but no transition animation. Range inputs use browser defaults with `accent-color` override.

### JSX Changes

**4a. Wrap each draft panel with motion.div.** For the draft note panel (line 2360), draft sticker panel (line 2429), and draft stamp panel (line 2466):

```jsx
// Wrap all three draft panel sections in a single AnimatePresence:
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
    {!isFocusMode && !isTimeCapsuleMode && draftNote && (
        <motion.div
            key="draft-note"
            className="fw-draft-note-panel"
            initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -12, scale: 0.98 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, scale: 1 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -8, scale: 0.98 }}
            transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 260, damping: 20 }}
        >
            {/* ...existing inner content unchanged... */}
        </motion.div>
    )}

    {!isFocusMode && !isTimeCapsuleMode && draftSticker && (
        <motion.div
            key="draft-sticker"
            className="fw-draft-note-panel"
            initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -12, scale: 0.98 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, scale: 1 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -8, scale: 0.98 }}
            transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 260, damping: 20 }}
        >
            {/* ...existing inner content unchanged... */}
        </motion.div>
    )}

    {!isFocusMode && !isTimeCapsuleMode && draftStamp && (
        <motion.div
            key="draft-stamp"
            className="fw-draft-note-panel"
            initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -12, scale: 0.98 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, scale: 1 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -8, scale: 0.98 }}
            transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 260, damping: 20 }}
        >
            {/* ...existing inner content unchanged... */}
        </motion.div>
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

Similarly wrap the selected note editor (line 2502) and selected item actions (line 2553):
```jsx
<AnimatePresence>
    {!isFocusMode && selectedNote && selectedItemCanEdit && activeTool !== "eraser" && !isTimeCapsuleMode && (
        <motion.div
            key="note-editor"
